Leopard Kills German Woman During TV Show Filming in Namibia, News24 Says

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-03-18T12:28:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/namibian-leopard-kills-46-year-old-german-woman-news24-says.html
A leopard killed a 46-year-old
German woman in  Namibia  who was part of a television crew for
ndF,  News24  said.  The leopard, which the German crew thought was tame, went
for the unidentified womanâ€™s throat during the filming of an
episode of Um Himmels Willen and she died at the scene, the
Johannesburg-based website said, citing Ulf Tubbesing, a vet who
owns the Namibian farm where the incident took place.  Tubbesing ordered his farm manager to shoot the leopard,
